data.chText: 变得重要（或突出）；起重要作用
data.enText: to be/become important and noticed by people; to play an important part

data.chText: 在危急时刻她总是挺身而出。
data.enText: She has always been to the fore at moments of crisis.

data.chText: 近几个月来这个问题又成为热点。
data.enText: The problem has come to the fore again in recent months.

data.chText: 使处于显要地位；使突出
data.enText: to make sth become noticed by people

data.chText: 在（船、飞行器或动物）前部的；在头部的
data.enText: located at the front of a ship, an aircraft or an animal

data.chText: 在（或向）船头；在（或向）飞行器头部
data.enText: at or towards the front of a ship or an aircraft

data.chText: 前方注意，看球（打高尔夫球时警告前面球路中的人以免被击中）
data.enText: used in the game of golf to warn people that they are in the path of a ball that you are hitting

means: 在(船、飞行器或动物)前部的
前方注意，看球(打高尔夫球时警告前面球路中的人以免被击中)
(打高尔夫球时的叫声)前面的人让开!

data.chText: 变得重要（或突出）；起重要作用
data.enText: to be/become important and noticed by people; to play an important part

data.chText: 在危急时刻她总是挺身而出。
data.enText: She has always been to the fore at moments of crisis.

data.chText: 近几个月来这个问题又成为热点。
data.enText: The problem has come to the fore again in recent months.

data.chText: 使处于显要地位；使突出
data.enText: to make sth become noticed by people

tr: front part of a vessel or aircraft
example: he pointed the bow of the boat toward the finish line

tr: near or toward the bow of a ship or cockpit of a plane
example: the captain went fore (or forward) to check the instruments

value.def: If someone or something comes to the fore in a particular situation or group, they become important or popular.

example.ex: A number of low-budget independent films brought new directors and actors to the fore.
example.tran: 许多低成本独立制作的电影使新导演和新演员崭露头角。

value.def: Fore is used to refer to parts at the front of an animal, ship, or aircraft.

example.ex: There had been no direct damage in the fore part of the ship.
example.tran: 船的前部没有受到直接破坏。

example.ex: ...a swelling appeared below his near fore knee.
example.tran: 左前腿膝关节下出现的一个肿块

value.tran: (动物、船只或飞行器)前部的，前端的

value.def: If something is fore in a boat or plane, it is at the front of it.

example.ex: Our yacht was well equipped with two double cabins fore and aft...
example.tran: 我们的游艇设施完备，首尾有两个双人舱。

example.ex: He loosened his very strong hold on the ship's rail and glanced fore and aft.
example.tran: 他松开紧紧抓住护栏的手，往船的两头扫了一眼。
